TY  - JOUR
T1  - Optimum No-Risk Strategy for Win-Place Pari-Mutuel Betting
AU  - Willis, Kenneth E.
Y1  - 1964/04/01
PY  - 1964
DA  - 1964/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.10.3.574
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.10.3.574
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 574
EP  - 577
VL  - 10
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The problem of finding an optimum, no-risk strategy for placing simultaneous win and place pari-mutuel bets is formulated in terms of a linear programming problem. For a basic feasible solution (i.e., a profitable schedule of bets) to exist, it is necessary for the win and place pools to weight the contestants differently. If the stake holder removes a fraction of the pool, then a solution is not guaranteed, but will exist if this difference in win-place weighting is sufficient. A simple example is presented.
AB  - The problem of finding an optimum, no-risk strategy for placing simultaneous win and place pari-mutuel bets is formulated in terms of a linear programming problem. For a basic feasible solution (i.e., a profitable schedule of bets) to exist, it is necessary for the win and place pools to weight the contestants differently. If the stake holder removes a fraction of the pool, then a solution is not guaranteed, but will exist if this difference in win-place weighting is sufficient. A simple example is presented.
